1:
God is our refuge and strength,
\q a very present help in trouble.
\q
2:
Therefore we will not fear, though the earth should change,
\q though the mountains should be shaken into the heart of the seas,
\q
3:
though its waters roar and rage, and
\q though the mountains tremble with their swelling.
\qs Selah\qs*
4:
There is a river, the streams of which make the city of God happy,
\q the holy place of the tabernacles of the Most High.
\q
5:
God is in the middle of her; she will not be moved;
\q God will help her, and he will do so at the dawn of morning.
8:
Come, behold the deeds of Yahweh,
\q the destruction he has caused on earth.
\q
46:
\m
\d For the chief musician. A psalm of the sons of Korah; set to Alamoth. A song.
\q
